Taiwan Stocks Movers Column: Motech Industries, TPK Holding

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-02-24T05:55:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/chunghwa-telecom-delta-first-financial-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taipei trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are the 1:30 p.m. closing trade.  Taiwan’s Taiex Index rose 12.70, or 0.2 percent, to
8,541.64, snapping three days of losses.    Motech Industries Inc . (6244 TT) increased 6.6 percent to
NT$129.50. The island’s largest solar-cell maker signed a
contract with the Suzhou unit of GCL Poly Energy Holdings Ltd.
to buy silicon wafers, the Taiwanese company said in a statement
to the stock exchange yesterday. Under the agreement, Motech
Industries may buy $1.03 billion of products through the end of
2015, according to the statement.  TPK Holding Co. (3673 TT) surged 6.9 percent to a record
NT$777. The supplier of touch-panels to Apple Inc. plans to
spend NT$20.3 billion this year, compared with NT$9.4 billion in
2010, Chief Financial Officer Freddie Liu said at an investors’
conference yesterday in Taipei.  “After TPK’s investor conference yesterday, investors are
more confident about the outlook for touch panel makers,” said
George Chang, an analyst at Yuanta Securities Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
 wlim26@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
